comments: The ball does not go out of bounds after Bridges (PHX) makes contact with it along the sideline.
Ayton (PHX) initiates contact with Jokic (DEN) along the sideline that causes him to lose his balance.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Harris' (DEN) path and does not deliver the contact.
Jokic (DEN) engages and disengages with Ayton (PHX) during rebounding.
Johnson (PHX) and Murray (DEN) make incidental foot-to-foot contact with one another off-ball.
Murray (DEN) and Johnson (PHX) engage and disengage with one another as they move over the screen.
Murray (DEN) establishes himself in a screening position in Ayton's (PHX) path and does not deliver the contact.
Bridges (PHX) turns slightly as he jumps alongside Murray's (DEN) path and absorbs the body contact made during the driving shot attempt.
Murray (DEN) makes contact across Bridges' (PHX) left arm after Bridges secures the rebound.
Ayton (PHX) legally contests Jokic's (DEN) jump shot attempt and makes incidental "high-five" contact with Jokic after the release.
Harris (DEN) has his hand rested on Paul's (PHX) right hip and marginal contact occurs as Harris swipes forward.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in a screening position in Bridges' (PHX) path and does not deliver the contact.

Crowder (PHX) raises his arm and some contact occurs with Murray's (DEN) head as Murray sets the screen. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in a screening position in Crowder's (PHX) path following the hand-off and does not deliver the contact.

Murray (DEN) gathers the ball with his right foot planted before his stepback.  He then plants his left foot as his first step, followed by his right foot as his second step, but then he takes another step with his left foot.
Ayton (PHX) moves to the side of Murray (DEN) during his jump shot attempt and Murray initiates the marginal contact by lifting his leg.
Paul (PHX) cleanly dislodges Porter Jr. (DEN) of the ball during rebounding.
Porter Jr. (DEN) makes incidental contact with Crowder's (PHX) lower half as Crowder secures the rebound.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in Morris' (DEN) path prior to contact taking place, which Ayton does not deliver.
Ayton (PHX) initiates contact with Jokic's (DEN) upper half that affects his FOM off ball.
Bridges (PHX) reflexively places his arm around Jokic's (DEN) upper half following the hand off and quickly removes it thereafter.
Crowder (PHX) brushes Morris' (DEN) upper half and marginal contact occurs as he drives toward the lane.
Kaminsky (PHX) and Jokic (DEN) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Kaminsky (PHX) jumps from point A to point B and initiates body contact with Jokic (DEN) that affects his put-back attempt.
Harris (DEN) and Nader (PHX) engage and disengage with one another as the pick expires.
Kaminsky (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Porter Jr.'s (DEN) path and does not deliver the contact.
Porter Jr. (DEN) applies a rested hand to Paul's (PHX) upper half following the release of his jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs.
Morris (DEN) is jumping to the side of Crowder (PHX) when he brushes Crowder's left leg and marginal contact occurs following the release of the jump shot attempt.
Kaminsky (PHX) and Jokic (DEN) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Kaminsky (PHX) makes contact across Jokic's (DEN) head during the driving shot attempt.
Harris (DEN) places his hands to Nader's (PHX) front and quickly removes them.
Nader (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Harris' (DEN) path and does not deliver the contact.
Kaminsky (PHX) slightly extends his lower body in Murray's (DEN) path as he sets the screen and marginal contact occurs.
Dozier (DEN) makes contact across Nader's (PHX) right arm/elbow during his upward shooting motion.
Kaminsky (PHX) makes contact to Jokic (DEN) while he is in his shooting motion.
Paul (PHX) has his arm around Dozier's (DEN) midsection as he sets the screen and slides it off as marginal contact occurs.
Jokic (DEN) and Kaminsky (PHX) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Harris (DEN) and Dozier (DEN) maintain legal guarding position as they defend Kaminsky (PHX) along the perimeter.
Kaminsky (PHX) and Jokic (DEN) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Harris (DEN) briefly grasps Kaminsky's (PHX) arm as he attempts to retrieve the pass, but it is cleanly deflected away.
